race.comment: There's been plenty to like about the two runs this spring from GINGER SINNER (5), who might be ready to peak third-up. The rise to 1250m looks ideal and, with the claim, he can settle in the first half of the field and finish powerfully. IL CUBO (3) is a dual acceptor and, if connections choose to send him to SA, he looks a definite danger. He showed enough in a recent jump out in between runs to forgive his below-par run last start. His prior form gives him a strong chance here. WELCOMETOTHESHOW (4) has done little wrong in his career and he was a track and distance winner earlier in the campaign. He will have to concede some ground from the wide barrier but he's got a big finish. Others for quaddies and exotics include CAPITALEX (8) and TAINO ROCKET (10).
